In the diagram, $AB$ and $CD$ are straight lines. What is the value of $x?$
\begin{center}
    \begin{asy}
    size(10cm);
    draw((0,0)--(12,0));
draw((0,5)--(12,5));
draw((3,0)--(5,5)--(9,0));
label("$60^\circ$",(5,4.5),W);
label("$50^\circ$",(5.5,4.5),E);
label("$A$",(0,5),W);
label("$C$",(0,0),W);
label("$B$",(12,5),E);
label("$D$",(12,0),E);
label("$120^\circ$",(3,0),NW);
label("$x^\circ$",(7.5,0),N);
    \end{asy}
\end{center}
}

\textbf{Answer:} Since $\angle AXB = 180^\circ,$ then$$\angle YXZ = 180^\circ - 60^\circ - 50^\circ = 70^\circ.$$Also,$$\angle XYZ = 180^\circ - \angle CYX = 180^\circ - 120^\circ = 60^\circ.$$Since the angles in $\triangle XYZ$ add to $180^\circ,$ then$$x^\circ = 180^\circ - 70^\circ - 60^\circ = 50^\circ,$$so $x=\boxed{50}.$
}
